  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study will evaluate if acupuncture is helpful in treating cancer-related fatigue in
      breast cancer patients undergoing radiation therapy.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Each participant will have a baseline visit before her radiation therapy begins to complete
      questionnaires. Participants will receive either true acupuncture or sham acupuncture twice
      per week for the six weeks of radiation therapy. She will have a short questionnaire at three
      weeks into her radiation, and she will complete questionnaires again at the end of her
      radiation and four weeks later.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
